Cons:
Functions do not run in a standard Node.js environment. It's a Node.js-like environment, polyfilled by unenv (Universal Node Environment). Because of this, not all Node.js APIs are supported. For example, I had to polyfill the crypto module for google-auth-library.
D1 uses SQLite, so it inherits all the quirks of SQLite. For instance, if you want to change a column's type, you have to create a new table, move the data to it, remove the previous table, and then rename the new table to the original table's name.
